				<td valign="bottom"><img src="/english/images/bbs_line.gif"></td>
                <td align="left" style="padding:5 10" width="388"><font class="title01">Firmly established the 2nd place in the high-function camera phone market</font> </td>
				<td valign="bottom"><img src="/english/images/bbs_line.gif"></td>
                <td width="100" align="center">Jun.17,2003</td>
              </tr>
			  <tr class="bbs05"> 
                <td height="1" colspan="5"><img src="/english/images/blank.gif"></td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bbs03"> 
                <td colspan="2" height="21" align="center">&nbsp;</td>
                <td colspan="3" align="left" style="padding:5 10">This year, Curitel Communications Inc. (President&CEO, Song, Moon-Seob, www.curitel.com) has sold 230,000 combined high-function camera phones in the domestic market, taking an average of 22% of market share and firmly establishing the 2nd place in the camera phone market.<br>
<br>
 According to an industry source, 1.02 million sets of embedded camera phones were sold between January and May of 2003. Among the sales, Samsung Electronics sold 552,000, Curitel sold 230,000, KTFT sold 140,000 and LG Electronics sold 98,000 handsets.<br>
<br>
 Especially, Curitel launched the high-function camera phone model at the end of March called “PS-E100” (for SKT 011 and 017 users), which has EV-DO, GPS and camera feature for the first time in Korea. The model sold 64,000 sets in May alone, marking 25% of market share by surpassing KTFT (10%) and LG Electronics (8%). Park Chang-Jin, Managing Director of Domestic Operations BU of Curitel said, “Total sales volume in the domestic market is still lower than that of LG. But I believe that we are surpassing LG in terms of overall products and brand price, as we take the 2nd place in high-function camera phones that indicate the future sales growth,” and added, “When 64-poly sound phone is launched this month, this trend is expected to accelerate.” <br>
<br>
 Last November, Curitel Communications Inc. became the first in Korea to launch 330,000-pixel camera phones, named “Curitel PD-6000” (for KTF 016 and 018 users) and “Curitel PD-K600” (for LGT 019 users). Consumers are showing high interest in these products and the two models boast the highest-pixel camera and offer diverse multi-media features such as video chatting and image editing, thus winning steady popularity among young users.<br>
<br>
 Especially, Curitel’s camera phone “PD-6000” has been designated as the Hall of Fame winner by the Cetizen (www.cetizen.com) that is a specialized community for cellular phone users. To be designated as Cetizen’s Hall of Fame winner, a handset model must win the first place in popularity votes of netizens for five weeks in a row. “Curitel PD-6000” was selected as the best handset by netizens for five weeks in a row from the fourth week of January till the fourth week of February this year. Netizens picked several performances of “PD-6000” as strong points: stereo LED located at the side of the product (when the bell rings or vibrates, two illuminators at both ears blink in blue), and the streamlined designing reminiscent of a sports car.<br>
 Curitel Communications Inc. introduced the first 64-poly “3D Sound Phone” in Korea early this month, and now plans to launch about 20 more high-function products this year including a mega-pixel camera phone during the second half of 2003.<br>
<br>
The Korea Economic Daily (June 17th, 2003)<br>
</td>
              </tr>
